Rostov 42

The Gate to the Caucasus ...
                                
Summer offensive, southern Russia, 1942

In the morning of July 21st, 1942, east of the Sambek area near Taganrog the Group Ruoff advanced on Rostov. After the break-through against insignificant reserve units the Germans approached the first defense line around Rostov.  
On July 22nd all troups were in their positions for the conquest of the city. The Russian troups, however, were entrenched and firmly decided to defend Rostov at any costs ...

